5:
I see. 
So you're saying you have no alibi.
8:
I'm tellin ya, it wasn't meeee! 
You've gotta believe meeee!
11:
It's not that I don't, ma'am. 
But part of my job is to find answers.
19:
NO! Say something, Alk! 
I need a witness on my side!
23:
Whoa... I didn't know the Guild Knights 
were in charge of investigations too.
26:
It's our duty to stop crime, 
and prevention plays a vital role. 
However, it's a burden that's becoming 
overladen, to say the least.
30:
I bet, with those suspicious characters 
popping up in the Kaleidoscope... 
Not to mention the marauding dragons 
and Farland stuff.
32:
Personally, my biggest concern is the 
orphans left behind by adventurers.
34:
However, the guild's current focus is 
ending the illegal trade of cursed gear.
39:
Oh, you mean like that place where 
you arrested us?
42:
Palpebra is a nation of commerce, 
so the exportation of goods from 
the Kaleidoscope isn't prohibited by 
law or anything.
43:
However, we must ensure that these 
wares don't pose a threat to society at 
large, especially those of unknown 
origin.
45:
However, it's been more difficult as of 
late to keep track of it all.
48:
Contraband slipping under the Guild's 
watchful eye, huh? 
That explains why Lelucia's here.
51:
Hey... You're supposed to be on my 
side, remember?!
54:
Yes, well, that and her frequent 
disappearances from Palpebra... 
although it all makes sense to me now.
58:
Yeah, like anyone was ever gonna 
believe I was traveling to other worlds!
60:
This was merely to satisfy my own 
curiosity. 
I made a promise to Light here that 
I would not divulge this information to 
anyone else.
62:
But we need to capture a suspect at 
once. So please, Mal Lelucia...
66:
Well, I diiiid hear through the grapevine 
about a fellow Sheephird involved in 
some shady biz...
77:
I appreciate you making the trip with 
me, Alk.
80:
I felt like I had to, especially after 
hearing that you'd be going on your 
own.
82:
I don't know if I'm Guild Knight material, 
but I'm glad to be of help, especially 
since you're short on people.
84:
Yes, well... without inducting you as 
a Guild Knight, I can't have you 
accompanying me in an official 
capacity.
86:
Regardless, it's faster this way if I grant 
you the title myself, seeing as your 
name, age, and origin are all unclear.
93:
Do not apologize. Too much humility 
can be self-destructive.
96:
I may have mistaken you for a criminal 
at first, but one doesn't become 
second-in-command without 
developing an eye for character.
98:
You're a talented swordsman, and 
more importantly, someone worth 
trusting in.
99:
Let's get moving. 
We're almost at our destination.
109:
This place appears to have been 
occupied until very recently—they 
must've known we were coming.
123:
Why... here?! Uh-oh... My body... won't... 
move!
126: O mighty light, I beseech thee!
131:
May your boundless wisdom shine 
upon us and illuminate our path!
138: What the... I feel so... powerful!
148: Looks like our perp really was here.
151:
I can't believe something like this could 
make its way out of the Kaleidoscope...
154:
It appears we may be dealing with 
shadier characters than initially 
thought.
156:
It's a good thing they left in a terrible 
hurry. There's a trove of evidence for us 
to dig through.
159:
This may be one of our biggest leads 
yet. Thank you, Alk.
163:
(We may have only just scratched the 
surface today...)
